<br>
Basically what happened is when they added crits to the game they made it so if at the time a spell takes effect (i.e. lands on a MOB) it checks to see if you are &quot;casting&quot; a right click item.  If that check fails you get the opportunity to do a crit roll and possibly crit that spell.<br>
<br>
Why this happens ona Burntwood Staff and not BoBC is that the BWS is a projectile and assuming your back a short distance you will finish &quot;casting&quot; the BWS by the time the bolt hits the MOB.  Therefore it has a chance to crit like a normal spell unlike the BoBC. <p><hr>
